snippet: At least 10 demonstrators and 29 police officers were injured on Saturday in one of eastern China’s biggest cities.
abstract: Huge demonstration against planned waste incinerator in eastern Chinese city of Hangzhou turns violent as protesters overturn and set fire to police cars, leaving at least 10 demonstrators and 29 police officers injured.
lead_paragraph: At least 10 demonstrators and 29 police officers were injured on Saturday in one of eastern China’s biggest cities.

headline.main: Protest of Planned Incinerator Turns Violent in Chinese City
headline.print_headline: Protest of Planned Incinerator Turns Violent in Chinese City
